  "A factory produces widgets with cost C(x) = 0.005x^3 - 0.5x^2 + 30x + 500. At what production level does marginal cost start increasing?": "",
  "x = 30 units": "",
  "x = 100/3 units": "",
  "x = 100 units": "",
  "x = 50 units": "",
  "MC = C'(x) = 0.015x^2 - x + 30. MC starts increasing when MC'(x) = C''(x) = 0.03x - 1 = 0, so x = 100/3 (approximately 33.3 units). This is an inflection point of the cost curve.": "",
  "A medicine degrades according to A(t) = A_0 * e^(-0.1t) mg. If 500 mg is administered and the effective dose is 200 mg, after how many hours does it become ineffective?": "",
  "ln(2.5)/0.1 hours": "",
  "30 hours": "",
  "5*ln(2) hours": "",
  "10*ln(5/2) hours": "",
  "200 = 500*e^(-0.1t). e^(-0.1t) = 2/5. -0.1t = ln(2/5) = -ln(5/2). t = 10*ln(5/2) hours (approximately 9.16 hours). Note: ln(5/2) = ln(2.5), so both first and second options represent the same value.": "",
